    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking, China</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 307.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm your cipher telegram
                    received April 29.<note n="a" xml:id="d265fna">Supra.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I have drawn up a form following closely the British bond and sent it to Mr.
                    Moir, the American delegate on the bankers’ commission in Shanghai. I have asked
                    him to make the necessary calculations and have the form printed as soon as
                    possible. When received I will forward it to the department for approval and
                    verification of the figures.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
